    "According to Kotz et al. (2022), a rise in the number of rainy days and excessive daily rainfall, as well as a nonlinear reaction to the total annual and averaged monthly variations in rainfall, slows economic growth rates.",
    "Apparently, numerous studies have identified connections between overall changes in temperature and economic growth either in short or long-term, but data on the relationship between within-year temperature variability and macroeconomic variables is scant (Donadelli et al. 2022); few studies have suggested that the relationship between climate uncertainty and economic outcomes is significant and very important (Burke et al. 2015; Pindyck 2021)."
